        <item xml:lang="zh">使者</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>OFFICIAL who is SENT by the GOVERNMENT to ACT:perform a TASK.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current formal word for an envoy is shǐ zhě 使者.</p>
<p>2. Shǐ/shì 使 can refer to an envoy.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>使者</p>
<p>使節</p>
<p>使君</p>
<p>使命</p>
<p>使人</p>
<p>使</p>
<p>星使</p>
<p>行使</p>
<p>大使</p>
<p>行李 refers to an ordinary messenger of less than diplomatic status.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
